2026-04-16 12:35:39 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['sensor-operated relay (control module)'] hypothesis_explanation="The relay in the control module should close and pass nearly the full 12V to the output terminals during the 'on' cycle, but instead, the voltage at the switched output remains at just 0.36V (relative to ground) even when the relay should be closed. This suggests the relay contacts are either internally faulty (fused or burnt contacts, loss of continuity) or another internal connection at the relay is open/high impedance. The power supply is fine, and the control module is receiving proper input voltage, ruling out upstream issues. The insensitivity of the output to potentiometer adjustments and the unchanged low output voltage confirm the relay is not functioning. All evidence points to a failed relay in the control module."
