description: Visually inspect and electrically test the printed circuit board traces and solder joints between the relay output contact and the Control Output Cable (+) terminal for any hairline cracks, cold solder joints, or PCB damage that could cause a severe voltage drop despite apparent continuity., outcome='The visual and electrical inspection found no observable faults or damage on the traces or solder joints between the relay and the Control Output Cable (+). Continuity from the Control Relay to the Control Output Cable (+) is confirmed with a low resistance of 0.01 Ω. However, voltage at the Control Output Cable (+) terminal is 0.3592 V, the same as its negative terminal, despite 11.9873 V being present at the relay, indicating a significant voltage drop along this path.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=95.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('test_path_continuity', 30.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module output terminals with load disconnected,
description: Disconnect the load module from the control module output terminals and measure the voltage at the control module output terminals (Control Output Cable + and −) with no load attached. This will determine if the voltage drop is due to a fault in the load module or excessive current draw., outcome='The attempt to disconnect the load module from the control module output terminals was not permitted in the current mode, so voltage readings were taken with the load still connected. The Control Output Cable (+) measured 0.3592 V, and the Control Output Cable (−) measured 0.0003 V.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('disconnect_cable', 0.0), ('disconnect_cable', 0.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> load module internal terminals (lamp and indicator branch) with power off,
description: With the system powered down, measure resistance across the main lamp, indicator lamp, and between the supply terminals in the load module to check for short circuits or abnormally low resistance that might indicate a fault in the load module causing excessive current draw and voltage collapse., outcome='All measured resistances are nominal: main lamp (120 Ω), internal indicator lamp (500 Ω), load input cable (+) (0.1 Ω), and load input cable (−) (0.1 Ω). No signs of short circuit or abnormally low resistance were found in the load module components. No polarity inversion was detected during these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=85.0, cost_breakdown=[('test_continuity', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control module internal wiring (insulation, for shorts to ground or other nets),
description: Test for possible internal shorts (partial or resistive, possibly through moisture or conductive debris) in the control module wiring from the relay output to ground or any other nets by measuring resistance and possible leakage current to ground with the system powered off., outcome='The resistance of the Control Relay is nominal at 0.01 Ω, which matches the expected value, and there is no measurable leakage current (0.0 A) with the system powered off. No internal shorts or leakage pathways to ground were detected during these tests.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=45.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_current', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Output Cable (+) and (-) at load module input terminals,
description: Measure the voltage at the input terminals of the load module (where the output cables from the control module connect to the load module) to see if the voltage is dropping somewhere between the control module output and the load module input, or if the voltage drop is already present at the load module connection. This can help pinpoint if the fault is in the cable or at the module interfaces., outcome='The voltage at Load Input Cable (+) is 0.3592 V, and at Load Input Cable (−) is 0.0003 V. No polarity inversion was detected in these measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control Output Cable (+) path (disconnected from load module),
description: Disconnect the Control Output Cable (+) from the load module and measure the voltage at the open end of the cable while the relay is engaged. This will determine if the voltage drop is caused by current draw from the load module or if it is present even under no load., outcome='The attempt to disconnect the Control Output Cable (+) was not permitted in the current mode. The measured voltage at the open end of Control Output Cable (+) is 0.3592 V, present at both positive and negative reference points.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=20.0, cost_breakdown=[('disconnect_cable', 0.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> Control module inspection – relay output trace and output connector,
description: With the inspection panel open, perform a point-to-point voltage and current test between the relay output (where 12V is present) and every subsequent physical point up to and including the actual pin of the output connector, using fine probes. The aim is to identify any point where the voltage drops from 12V to the observed 0.3592V, especially focusing on any hidden PCB vias, internal split traces, or mechanical interfaces that could be intermittently fractured or corroded despite showing continuity at low currents. Try increasing test current (with an external load) if possible, to stress the path for hidden resistance., outcome='The inspection panel could not be opened as it does not have the affordance OPENABLE. Voltage at the Control Relay output is 11.9873 V on one port and 0.3592 V on the other; current through the relay and output cable is 0.0 A. At the Control Output Cable (+), both measured points show 0.3592 V, indicating a voltage drop occurs between the relay and the cable, with no current flowing in the circuit.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=85.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_current', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_current', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
